paragraphs.title: Download Files (Sherlock Homes Series and Stop Words from Stanford NLP)
paragraphs.text:
%sh

#remove existing copies of dataset from HDFS
hadoop fs -rm /tmp/big.txt
hadoop fs -rm /tmp/stop.txt

#fetch the dataset
wget http://norvig.com/big.txt -O /tmp/big.txt
wget --no-check-certificate https://raw.githubusercontent.com/stanfordnlp/CoreNLP/master/data/edu/stanford/nlp/patterns/surface/stopwords.txt -O /tmp/stop.txt


#put data into HDFS

hadoop fs -put /tmp/big.txt /tmp
hadoop fs -ls -h /tmp/big.txt

hadoop fs -put /tmp/stop.txt /tmp
hadoop fs -ls -h /tmp/stop.txt

rm /tmp/big.txt
rm /tmp/stop.txt

paragraphs.title: Define function to remove puntion and numbers
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

import re



def removePunctuation(text):
    """Removes punctuation, changes to lower case, and strips leading and trailing spaces.

    Note:
        Only spaces, letters, and numbers should be retained.  Other characters should should be
        eliminated (e.g. it's becomes its).  Leading and trailing spaces should be removed after
        punctuation is removed.

    Args:
        text (str): A string.

    Returns:
        str: The cleaned up string.
    """    
    return re.sub('[^a-zA-Z ]','',text).strip().lower()

def wordCount(wordListRDD):
    """Creates a pair RDD with word counts from an RDD of words.

    Args:
        wordListRDD (RDD of str): An RDD consisting of words.

    Returns:
        RDD of (str, int): An RDD consisting of (word, count) tuples.
    """
    return (wordListRDD
           .map(lambda w: (w,1))
           .reduceByKey(add).sortBy( lambda x: -x[1]))

%pyspark

input_file = "hdfs:///tmp/big.txt"
stop_file = "hdfs:///tmp/stop.txt"


textRDD = sc.textFile(input_file, 8).map(removePunctuation)
stopWords = set(sc.textFile(stop_file).collect())

print '\n'.join(textRDD
                .zipWithIndex()  # to (line, lineNum)
                .map(lambda (l, num): '{0}: {1}'.format(num, l))  # to 'lineNum: line'
                .take(15))

%pyspark

top15WordsAndCounts = wordCount(filteredTextWordsRDD).take(15)
print '\n'.join(map(lambda (w, c): '{0}: {1}'.format(w, c), top15WordsAndCounts))
